OL,6,F"It is clear from the inquest that
OL,7,Feveryone did their best to care for
OL,8,Fhim, and there is no evidence that Mr
OL,9,FCampbell's death could have been
OL,10,Favoided.
OL,12,F"We are committed to constantly
OL,13,Fimproving the quality of care we
OL,14,Fprovide to our patients.
OL,16,F"Whilst there are aspects of Mr
OL,17,FCampbell's care that could have been
OL,18,Fimproved, the coroner has found that
OL,19,Fthese did not more than minimally
OL,20,Fcontribute to his sad death.
